[{"id":"VR732299","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><include href=\"../Passage/VR732294.qti.xml\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\"></include></div><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a diagram with two boxes that are touching each other. The box on the left consists of a particulate representation of H 2, gas, and the box on the right consists of a particulate representation of C l 2, gas. H atoms are represented by unshaded circles and C l atoms are represented by shaded circles. The diagram representing H 2, gas, contains four identical molecules. Each molecule is made up of two H atoms. The diagram representing C l 2, gas, contains five identical molecules. Each molecule is made up of two C l atoms.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR732299.g22.svg\"/></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">The diagrams show particulate representations for samples of gaseous <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"H 2\"><math alttext=\"H 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mtext>H</mtext><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C l 2\"><math alttext=\"C l 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mtext>Cl</mtext><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span> separated by a barrier. After the barrier is removed, the gases react. Which of the following diagrams best represents the mixture if the reaction goes to completion?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR732299_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<div class=\"stimulus_reference\" xmlns=\"http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/apip/apipv1p0/qtiitem/imsqti_v2p2\" xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><p class=\"passage_para\">Gaseous hydrogen and gaseous chlorine can react to form hydrogen chloride gas, as represented by the following equation.</p><p class=\"standalone_statement style:1\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"H 2, gas, plus C l 2, gas, react to produce 2 H C l, gas\"><math alttext=\"H 2, gas, plus C l 2, gas, react to produce 2 H C l, gas\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mtext>H</mtext><mn>2</mn></msub><mpadded><mo>(</mo><mpadded><mtext mathvariant=\"italic\">g</mtext></mpadded><mo>)</mo></mpadded><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>Cl</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mpadded><mo>(</mo><mpadded><mtext mathvariant=\"italic\">g</mtext></mpadded><mo>)</mo></mpadded><mo>→</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>HCl</mtext><mpadded><mo>(</mo><mpadded><mtext mathvariant=\"italic\">g</mtext></mpadded><mo>)</mo></mpadded></math></span></span></p></div></div></div>"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a large box that contains four identical molecules. Each molecule is made up of one H atom and one C l atom.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR732299.g27.svg\"/></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a large box that contains eight identical molecules. Each molecule is made up of one H atom and one C l atom.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR732299.g28.svg\"/></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a large box that contains nine molecules. Eight molecules are made up of one H atom and one C l atom. One molecule is made up of two C l atoms.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR732299.g29.svg\"/></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a large box that contains nine molecules. Seven molecules are made up of one H atom and one C l atom. One molecule is made up of two H atoms. One molecule is made up of two C l atoms.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR732299.g30.svg\"/></span></p>"],"answer":2}]